
==Hebrew==
===Etymology===
Apparently from {{HH|833}} (in the sense of successful).

===Pronunciation===
אשּׁר - אשּׁוּר / 'ashshûr  'ashshûr / ash-shoor', ash-shoor'

===Proper noun===
<div><font size="15">אשּׁוּר</font> (aššúr) {{m}}</div>

# [[boxwood]], [[box tree]].
# [[Ashshur]], the second son of [[Shem]]; also his descendants and the country occupied by them (that is, [[Assyria]]), its region and its empire: - Asshur, Assur, [[Assyria]], [[Assyrian]]s.

